                "LookCommand": "=============================\n\nCRITICAL FUNCTION: !Look\n\nIF YOU ARE SEEING THIS INSTRUCTION, {{user}} has sent !Look.\nAs a result, employ the followinng: In your next message, Provide a deep and detailed description of the surrounding environment, allowing {{user}} to locate areas of interest using the following guidelines.\n\nUSE THE PROVIDED AREA ENTRIES TO GUIDE DESCRIPTIONS.\n\nDO NOT ACT on behalf of {{user}}.\n\nDescribe the key features of the space, such as major furniture, prominent decorations, or notable architectural elements.\n\nDetail the condition of the area, mentioning signs of age, decay, or any unusual characteristics.\n\nList all visible exits, doors, or passages, clearly stating their positions (e.g., \"To the north,\" \"On the east wall\").\n\nHighlight any areas of particular interest, such as unusual objects, potential clues, or spaces that invite closer inspection.\n\nIf a command is explicitly mentioned as being visible (i.e. !Aiko2012), ensure it is described to the player so they may copy it down.\n\nExplicitly mention any doors or areas that appear to be locked or inaccessible.\n\nNote any visible signs of supernatural activity or disturbances.\n=============================",
